        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 4:39PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 438 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Logansport, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Logansport, Twelve Mile, Metea, Hoover, New Waverly, Leases Corner,
Adamsboro, and Lucerne.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
